---
import Stage from '../layouts/Stage.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site.ts';

const description =
  'Privacy Policy for Rhine Media — how we collect, use, store and disclose your personal data when you visit our website or engage our services.';
---

<Stage title="Privacy Policy" description={description} pageH={5411}>
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(to bottom,#422b7f,#080129 73.682%);z-index:0"></div>

  <div style="position:absolute;left:195px;top:229px;width:572px;z-index:2;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:50px">
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:35px">
      <p style="font-weight:600;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#fff">Legal</p>
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:70px;line-height:1.3;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">Privacy<br>Policy</h1>
      <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#895dff">Last updated: {site.legalUpdated} — effective immediately</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:rgba(44,27,94,0.2);border:1px solid #fff;border-radius:30px;padding:30px;width:513px"><p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6)">This Privacy Policy describes how Rhine Media ("we", "our", "us"), operating at rhine-media.com, collects, uses, stores and discloses information about you when you visit our website or engage with our services. We are committed to protecting your privacy in accordance with applicable data protection legislation.</p></div>
  </div>

  <div style="position:absolute;left:839px;top:277px;width:886px;z-index:2;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:30px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.8;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6)">
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">1. Information We Collect</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>We may collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">Contact information: Name, email address, phone number, company name and role — collected when you submit our contact form or initiate a cooperation inquiry;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Communication data: Messages, emails and chat records exchanged with our team for the purposes of service delivery;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Technical data: IP address, browser type and version, operating system, referral source, pages viewed and time spent — collected automatically via cookies and analytics tools;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Business data: Information about your offers, verticals, campaign objectives and budgets — provided by you in the context of a commercial relationship;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Financial data: Billing details and payment information necessary to process invoices and manage the commercial relationship (we do not store full card data).</li></ul><p>We do not knowingly collect personal data from individuals under the age of 18. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such data, please contact us immediately.</p></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">2. How We Use Your Information</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>We use the data we collect for the following purposes:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">To respond to enquiries and communicate with potential and existing clients;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To set up, manage, optimise and report on advertising campaigns;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To fulfil contractual obligations and deliver agreed services;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To process invoices and manage billing;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To improve our website, services and user experience;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To detect, prevent and address fraud, security issues and technical problems;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To comply with applicable legal obligations;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">To send service-related communications where required.</li></ul><p>We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. We do not use your data for unsolicited marketing without your explicit consent.</p></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">3. Legal Basis for Processing</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>Where applicable data protection law requires a legal basis for processing personal data, we rely on the following:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">Contract: Processing necessary to perform a contract with you, or to take steps at your request before entering a contract;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Legitimate interests: Processing necessary for our legitimate business interests, including responding to enquiries, improving our services and maintaining business relationships, where such interests are not overridden by your rights;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Legal obligation: Processing required to comply with applicable laws;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Consent: Where you have given specific, informed consent for a particular use of your data, which you may withdraw at any time.</li></ul></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience and collect analytics data. Cookies we may use include:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">Essential cookies: Required for the website to function properly. These cannot be disabled;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Analytics cookies: Help us understand how visitors interact with our website (e.g. Google Analytics). These are only set with your consent;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Preference cookies: Remember your settings and preferences for future visits.</li></ul><p>You can control and disable cookies through your browser settings. Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of our website.</p></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">5. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>We may share your information with carefully selected third parties in the following circumstances:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">Service providers: Trusted vendors who assist us in operating our business (e.g. hosting providers, analytics platforms, communication tools), bound by confidentiality obligations;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Advertising platforms: Ad networks and platforms (e.g. Google, Meta, TikTok) through which we operate campaigns on your behalf — governed by their own privacy policies;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Professional advisors: Lawyers, accountants and auditors under obligations of confidentiality;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Legal authorities: Where required by law, regulation, court order or government request;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Business transfers: In connection with a merger, acquisition or sale of assets, where we will notify you before your data is transferred and becomes subject to a different policy.</li></ul><p>All third parties we work with are required to maintain appropriate security standards and to process your data only in accordance with our instructions and applicable law.</p></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">6. International Data Transfers</h2><p>As a global agency, we may transfer your personal data to countries outside your home jurisdiction. Where such transfers occur, we take appropriate steps to ensure an adequate level of protection, including the use of Standard Contractual Clauses approved by relevant data protection authorities, or relying on adequacy decisions where available.</p></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">7. Data Retention</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes for which it was collected, including for the purposes of satisfying any legal, accounting or reporting requirements.</p><p>In general, we retain:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">Client contact and business data for the duration of the relationship plus 5 years;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Financial and billing records as required by applicable law (typically 7 years);</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Website analytics data for up to 26 months;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Correspondence and communications for up to 3 years from last contact.</li></ul></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">8. Data Security</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>We implement appropriate technical and organisational security measures to protect your personal data against unauthorised access, accidental loss, destruction or disclosure. These measures include encryption, access controls, secure servers and regular security reviews.</p><p>While we strive to protect your personal data, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security, and we encourage you to take appropriate steps to protect your own information.</p></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">9. Your Rights</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:26px"><li style="line-height:1.8">Right of access: To request a copy of the personal data we hold about you;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Right to rectification: To request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Right to erasure: To request deletion of your personal data in certain circumstances;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Right to restriction: To request that we limit the processing of your data;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Right to portability: To receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Right to object: To object to processing based on legitimate interests;</li><li style="line-height:1.8">Right to withdraw consent: Where processing is based on consent, to withdraw it at any time.</li></ul><p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details on our <a href="https://rhine-media.com/contact.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);text-decoration:underline">Contact page</a>. We will respond to all verified requests within 30 days. We may ask for proof of identity before processing sensitive requests.</p></div></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">10. Third-Party Websites</h2><p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those sites, and we are not responsible for their privacy practices. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.</p></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">11. Changes to This Policy</h2><p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology or applicable laws. When we make material changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p></section>
    <section style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px"><h2 style="font-family:var(--font-manrope);font-weight:800;font-size:25px;line-height:1.5;color:#edf0fa;margin:0">12. Contact Us</h2><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px"><p>If you have any questions, concerns or requests relating to this Privacy Policy or our data processing practices, please contact our team via our <a href="https://rhine-media.com/contact.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);text-decoration:underline">Contact page</a>. For data protection-related enquiries, you may also contact us directly via email. We are committed to addressing all privacy concerns promptly and transparently.</p><p>If you are located in the European Economic Area and believe your data protection rights have been violated, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority in your country of residence.</p></div></section>
  </div>
</Stage>
